# Solicitation Summary Report: 70CMSW26I00000001

---

## Overview
- **Title:** Boxed Meals at Broadview IL
- **Solicitation Number:** 70CMSW26I00000001
- **Agency:** Department of Homeland Security, US Immigration and Customs Enforcement (ICE), Mission Support Washington
- **Location:** ICE Detention Facility, Broadview, Illinois
- **Posted Date:** November 7, 2025
- **Response Due Date:** November 11, 2025, at 12:00 PM (Eastern Time)
- **Source/URL:** [sam.gov Posting](https://sam.gov/workspace/contract/opp/2c07aa2cdd6841e781b26767aac1fdcf/view)

---

## Scope of Work
- Provide 70 boxed meals for breakfast, lunch, and dinner (210 meals total daily) for detainees.
- Meals must:
  - Meet USDA Recommended Dietary Allowance (RDA) for calories, macronutrients, vitamins, and minerals.
  - Reflect nutritional balance: Breakfast (protein, whole grains, fruit, dairy); Lunch/Dinner (protein entr√©e, whole grains, vegetables, fruit, beverage).
  - Include vegetarian, low-sodium, gluten-free, and nut-free options as needed.
  - Be packaged individually in eco-friendly, disposable containers with clear labeling (meal type & prep date).
- Delivery requirements: Temperature-controlled vehicles at 6:00 AM (breakfast), 12:00 PM (lunch), and 6:00 PM (dinner).
- Meals prepared in a licensed, inspected kitchen by trained staff.
- Period of performance: 3 months from award date; possible extension.

---

## Compliance and Quality Assurance
- Weekly menu plans required and subject to government approval.
- Advance government approval needed for menu substitutions/changes.
- Government may inspect meals, staff, and delivery process at any time.
- Staff must be trained in food safety and handling; background checks required.
- Precise recordkeeping required (meal prep, delivery, and compliance).

---

## Insurance Requirements
- **Not specified in the provided summary.** Standard government expectations (general liability, food safety, worker's comp) likely, but details must be confirmed in the full document package.

---

## Invoicing and Payment
- Monthly billing, verifiable by delivery and compliance with requirements.

---

## Submission & Contact Information
- Capability statement and company data (business size, UEI, etc.) required.
- Key contacts not specified; refer to sam.gov posting for official instructions and questions.
- All bids must comply with submission directions as listed on sam.gov.

---

## Key Considerations
- Tight response window (approx. 4 calendar days from release).
- Thorough compliance demanded for menu content, food safety, labeling, and delivery timing.
- Prime for vendors with strong food logistics capacity, licensed kitchens, and experience with institutional food programs.
- Clarify insurance and any additional regulatory requirements before proposing.

